# JUMO — Deployment & Update Guide
### Railway (proxy) + GitHub auto-deploy

---

## Architecture

```
Tester browser
    ↓  loads page
Railway (serves public/index.html + public/personas.js)
    ↓  POST /api/messages + access token
Railway (Express proxy — server.js)
    ↓  adds API key, forwards
Anthropic API
```

Your API key never touches the browser.  
Testers authenticate with a shared access token you choose.  
**Personas live in `public/personas.js` — the only file you ever update.**

---

## Repo structure

```
jumo-proxy/
├── server.js              ← Express proxy (don't touch)
├── package.json
├── .gitignore
└── public/
    ├── index.html         ← UI shell (don't touch)
    └── personas.js        ← ALL persona data lives here ← THIS IS WHAT YOU UPDATE
```

---

## First-time deployment

### 1. Push to GitHub

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "JUMO v1.5"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/jumo-proxy.git
git push -u origin main
```

### 2. Deploy on Railway

1. **railway.app** → New Project → Deploy from GitHub repo → select `jumo-proxy`
2. Railway detects Node.js and deploys automatically
3. Go to **Variables** tab and set:

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | `sk-ant-your-key-here` |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN` | any password (share this with testers) |

4. Go to **Settings → Networking → Generate Domain** to get your public URL

Test it: `https://your-url.up.railway.app/health` → should return `{"status":"ok"}`

### 3. Share with testers

Send them:
- **URL:** `https://your-url.up.railway.app`
- **Access token:** whatever you set as `ACCESS_TOKEN`

---

## Updating personas after a session

This is the only thing you'll do regularly. Two steps.

**Step 1 — Generate updated `personas.js`**

Upload your updated corpus file to Claude and say:

> "Read the latest validated sections in this corpus and generate me an updated personas.js file for the JUMO test shell. Use the existing personas.js as the base — only update what the corpus has validated."

Claude outputs a new `personas.js`.

**Step 2 — Push to GitHub**

```bash
# Replace public/personas.js with the new file Claude gave you, then:
git add public/personas.js
git commit -m "personas: update from corpus session 5"
git push
```

Railway auto-detects the push and redeploys in ~2 minutes.  
All testers see the updated personas on next page refresh.  
**No HTML changes. No server changes. No redeployment config.**

---

## Updating broadcast questions

Same process — the questions are at the bottom of `personas.js`:

```javascript
var BROADCAST_QUESTIONS = [
  "question 1",
  "question 2",
  ...
];
```

Edit → push → done.

---

## Cost estimate

**Railway Hobby:** $5/month  
**Anthropic API:** ~$0.003–0.005 per message (claude-sonnet-4)  
10 testers × 20 messages + 5 broadcasts each ≈ **$2–4 total**

Set a hard monthly limit: Anthropic Console → Limits → Set monthly budget.

**Rate limiting:** 60 requests per IP per 15 minutes (edit `max` in `server.js` to change).

---

## Changing the access token

Railway Variables tab → update `ACCESS_TOKEN` → Railway restarts automatically.  
No code push needed.
